rs are peer-evaluated frequently in their careers. By introducing mentorship early, this course prepares them for professional practice. It also requires them to reflect on how to assess interpreting competence.',0),(2940,100,'5820','Documentation & Professional Practice I',3,'Students learn how to prepare themselves for assignments of different types, to be aware of the main social, political, and financial debates that interpreters deal with, and to navigate the paraprofessional variables (ethics, professional role) that frame their work.',0),(2941,100,'5825','Documentation & Professional Practice IV',3,'Students learn how to prepare themselves for assignments of different types, to be aware of the main social, political, and financial debates that interpreters deal with, and to navigate the paraprofessional variables (ethics, professional role) that frame their work.',0),(2942,100,'5830','Documentation & Professional Practice II',3,'Students learn how to prepare themselves for assignments of different types, to be aware of the main social, political, and financial debates that interpreters deal with, and to navigate the paraprofessional variables (ethics, professional role) that frame their work.',0),(2943,100,'5835','Documentation & Professional Practice V',3,'Students learn how to prepare themselves for assignments of different types, to be aware of the main social, political, and financial debates that interpreters deal with, and to navigate the paraprofessional variables (ethics, professional role) that frame their work.',0),(2944,100,'5840','Documentation &Professional Practice III',3,'Students learn how to prepare themselves for assignments of different types, to be aware of the main social, political, and financial debates that interpreters deal with, and to navigate the paraprofessional variables (ethics, professional role) that frame their work.',0),(2945,100,'5845','Documentation & Professional Practice VI',3,'Students learn how to prepare themselves fo